<div data-role="page" id="ADmulti">
	<div data-role="header">
		<h1>Art and Design: Multidisciplinary</h1>
	</div>
	<div data-role="content">
	  <p>The College has an established reputation for facilitating the creative development of art and design students. This course was developed in response to students who may wish to continue to study in more than one art/design/craft discipline over the three years of their degree programme. The course offers you a broad-based experience of contemporary visual and material arts practice and allows you to negotiate and develop a more personalised programme of study within speColeg Sir Gart areas of art and design to suit your own particular interests and needs (subject to timetabling requirements). </p>
	  <p>From the onset of the course you will have opportunities to gain experiences from a range of disciplines within the Applied Arts, Design and Fine Art programmes. Your chosen areas of study may combine electives from within the individual disciplines in order to facilitate practice that seeks to continue to work in more than one discrete area. Many Post-graduate teacher training courses (PGCE) expect prospective students to have experience across a range of art and design activities in addition to their own speColeg Sir Gart area. Students will develop a knowledge and understanding of exciting developments within international contemporary art, applied arts and design, its contexts and markets. Professional practice and enterprise skills teaching will help prepare students for employment and self employment options. </p>
	  <p>Your practice is supported by an integrated theory programme enabling you to work confidently and professionally within the context of Multidisciplinary Art and Design. The School of Creative Arts provides a friendly and supportive environment for students to explore their options and develop their individual style and potential</p>
	  <p><strong>Award</strong></p>
	  <ul>
	    <li>BA (Single Honours)</li>
      </ul>
	  <p><strong>UCAS Code</strong></p>
	  <ul>
	    <li>C22</li>
      </ul>
	  <p><strong>Language Choice</strong></p>
	  <ul>
	    <li>English</li>
      </ul>
	  <p><strong>Course Length</strong></p>
	  <ul>
	    <li>3 years full-time; part-time study available</li>
      </ul>
	  <p><strong>Entry Requirements</strong></p>
	  <ul>
	    <li>	      Tariff Score Points accepted 120	      </li>
	    <li>In addition applicants would normally be expected to have achieved English or Welsh language, Mathematics to a minimum of C at GCSE</li>
	  </ul>
	  <p><strong>Typical Modules</strong></p>
	  <p><strong>Department</strong></p>
	  <ul>
	    <li>School of Creative Arts</li>
      </ul>
