<div data-role="page" id="fineArtPDP">
	<div data-role="header">
		<h1>Fine Art: Painting, Drawing and Printmaking</h1>
	</div>
	<div data-role="content">
	  <p>This course is a speColeg Sir Gart programme that offers a diverse, thorough and dynamic experience of Fine Art Painting, Drawing and Printmaking. Students will be encouraged to develop a personal and independent art practice that critically interrogates the subject areas and explores these disciplines in relation to the rich historical and contemporary contexts. Skills based teaching underpins year one of the programme. </p>
	  <p>Through extensive exploration of traditional and contemporary materials and methods we aim to equip students with a comprehensive understanding of the craft of painting, drawing and printmaking whilst developing and nurturing personal visual language and conceptual concerns through guided experimentation, critical debate and analysis of studio practice. </p>
	  <p>During years two and three, students will develop a more independent art practice pursuing their own particular interests and concerns through negotiated projects with strong tutorial support. Students are encouraged to develop their own vision and consolidate their work, leading to a final year exhibition. Students can develop personal practice using a combination of painting, drawing and printmaking processes or they may choose to speColeg Sir Gare in one area as their practice evolves.Practical modules are supported by an integrated theory programme enabling students to work confidently and professionally within the context of Painting, Drawing and Printmaking.The course also includes enterprise and professional skills modules to help students achieve their career ambitions. </p>
	  <p>The School of Creative Arts provides a friendly and supportive environment for students to explore their options and develop their individual style and potential. The college has an established reputation for facilitating the creative development of art and design students, and the course continues to evolve in response to contemporary art, culture and technological innovation.</p>
