	    <li>Mature applicants with relevant prior experience are welcome and are considered on an individual basis. </li>
	    <li>International students will be interviewed by video conferencing. </li>
	    <li>At interview the candidate will give evidence of current experience and reasons for undertaking undergraduate study. He/she must demonstrate at interview that he/she is academically and technically/practically capable of completing and benefiting from the programme.</li>
	    <li>Academic certificates and relevant documentation will be checked before unconditional acceptance. Successful applicants will be accepted either conditionally or unconditionally, depending on whether they fulfil the academic requirements.</li>
	  </ul>
	  <p><strong>Typical Modules</strong></p>
	  <ul>
	    <li>Darkroom Photography</li>
	    <li>Digital Photography</li>
	    <li>Portrait Photography</li>
	    <li>Location Photography</li>
	    <li>Studio Photography</li>
	    <li>Live Projects and Competition</li>
	    <li>Major Project</li>
      </ul>
	  <p><strong>Department</strong></p>
	  <ul>
	    <li>School of Creative Arts</li>
      </ul>
	  <p><strong>Campus</strong></p>
	  <ul>
	    <li>Jobs Well</li>
      </ul>
	  <p><strong>Career Opportunities</strong></p>
	  <ul>
	    <li>The School and each of the programmes has a pro-active approach to encouraging personal professional development, through portfolio building, career skills development, and includes initiatives linked to entrepreneurialship, for example during the second and third years, you will be encouraged to participate in competitions and exhibitions as part of your programme.</li>
	    <li>You will be taught to write professional CV&rsquo;s, Artists Statements, applications for residencies etc. The Photography programme has many former graduates who have developed careers across a wide spectrum of activities and image-based industries, for recognised employers and as freelance photographers. </li>
	    <li>There is potential for further study at post-graduate level in Photography and the visual arts sector:
	      <ul>
	        <li>Fashion Photographer</li>
	        <li>Documentary Photographer</li>
	        <li>Photo Journalism</li>
	        <li>Advertising Photographer</li>
	        <li>Stills Photographer for film and television</li>
	        <li>Wildlife / Landscape Photographer</li>
	        <li>Fine Art Photographer</li>
	        <li>Lecturer</li>
	        <li>Related postgraduate study.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
	  <p><strong>Key Features</strong></p>
	  <ul>
	    <LI>Small class sizes in all modules</LI>
	    <LI>Access to excellent facilities and equipment </LI>
	    <LI>Strong vocational relevance and links with employers </LI>
	    <LI>Regular educational visits to exhibitions and events </LI>
	    <LI>Opportunities to pursue your own areas of interest </LI>
	    <LI>Final year major project on your subject choice </LI>
      </ul>
	  <p>&nbsp;</p>
    
    </div>
	<div data-role="footer">
		<li><a href="#creativeArtsUndergradCourses">Return</a></li>
